# Slide Code & Preview Components

Use the reusable slide components from `slides/components` instead of manual FlexBox/Box/CodePane/HtmlPreview layouts.

## When to Use Which

| Component | Use case |
|-----------|----------|
| **CodeAndPreviewSlide** | Code on the left, live HTML/CSS preview on the right (side-by-side) |
| **CodeSlide** | Code only, no preview (optionally children like Text below) |
| **PreviewSlide** | Live preview only, no code |
| **MiraContentSlide** | Custom content (lists, text, mixed) — use CodePane directly only when layout differs (e.g. centered) |

## CodeAndPreviewSlide

```jsx
<CodeAndPreviewSlide
  heading="Title"
  code={`<p>HTML here</p>`}
  preview={{ html: `<p>HTML here</p>`, css: `p { color: red; }`, title: 'Preview' }}
  // or shorthand: preview={`<p>HTML</p>`}
  language="html"
  showLineNumbers
  fontSize={12}
  notes="Presenter notes."
/>
```

## CodeSlide

```jsx
<CodeSlide
  heading="Title"
  code={`<tag>content</tag>`}
  language="html"
  fontSize={15}
  notes="Notes."
>
  <Text marginTop={16}>Optional content below code</Text>
</CodeSlide>
```

## PreviewSlide

```jsx
<PreviewSlide
  heading="Title"
  html={`<p>Content</p>`}
  css={``}
  title="Preview"
  notes="Notes."
/>
```

## Do Not

- Use manual `FlexBox` + `Box` + `CodePane` + `HtmlPreview` for side-by-side layouts
- Use `overflowX: 'auto'` — components use word-wrap by default
- Repeat CodePane theme/fontSize — components use oneLight and sensible defaults
